cardano/transaction/OutputReference.title: OutputReference
cardano/transaction/OutputReference.description:
An `OutputReference` is a unique reference to an output on-chain. The `output_index`
 corresponds to the position in the output list of the transaction (identified by its id)
 that produced that output

entity_registry/types/Entity.title: Entity
entity_registry/types/Entity.description:
Types for the Entity Registry contract
 These types represent the core data structures used for SACCO entities and their members
 SACCO entity metadata

governance/types/ProposalStatus.title: ProposalStatus
governance/types/ProposalStatus.description:
Types for the Governance contract
 These types represent the core data structures used for decision-making 
 processes within a SACCO entity
 Proposal status enumeration

treasury_management/types/SerializableVa.title: SerializableValue
treasury_management/types/SerializableVa.description:
Types for the Treasury Management contract
 These types represent the core data structures used for financial operations
 in a SACCO entity
 Serializable representation of Value for on-chain storage
 Instead of using the opaque Value type directly, we use a serializable
 representation that can be converted to/from Value when needed
